    "body": "hmm... If I change the Request from GET to POST, the referer get's finally transmitted.\n\nA workaround would look like this:\nModify `index.php` from my first commit to the following:\n\n#### index.php\n\n```\n<?php\nerror_log(array_key_exists('HTTP_REFERER', $_SERVER) ? \"YES\" : \"NO\");\necho\n'<html>\n    <head>\n        <script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"//code.jquery.com/jquery-1.11.3.min.js\"></script>\n\n        <script>\n            $(document).click(function(event) {\n                var href = $(event.target).attr(\"href\");\n\n                if (href != undefined)\n                {\n                    event.preventDefault();\n                    $(\"<form action=\\'\" + href + \"\\' method=\\'POST\\'></form>\").submit();\n                }\n            });\n        </script>\n    </head>\n    <body>\n        <p>HTTP_REFERER: ' . (array_key_exists('HTTP_REFERER', $_SERVER) ? \"YES: \" . $_SERVER['HTTP_REFERER'] : \"NO\") .'</p>\n        <a href=\"/index.php'\">click</a>\n    </body>\n</html>';\n```\n\nElectron will display this after clicking on the link:\n\n```\nHTTP_REFERER: YES: http://localhost/index.php\n\nclick\n```\n\nHTTP-Serverlog will also response with `YES`s.\n\n@zcbenz is this the normal procedure to receive the referer?\n"
